{
  "texts": [
    "The feasibility of automated extraction of perceived traits exposes a potential privacy threat 52.",
    "Word embeddings may contain information about traits that the target would prefer to keep private.",
    "Even if there are no explicit cues in the training data, the models may still be able to extract intimate information.",
    "This mirrors privacy threats pertaining to other data types.",
    "For example, people are not very accurate when predicting others' intimate traits from their facial images or Facebook Likes and thus do not perceive such data as overly sensitive."
  ]
}